OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FRail fares in England to   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Frise by up to 5.9%         
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Regulated rail fares in England will   
OL,6, rise by up to 5.9% from March, the     
OL,7, Department for Transport has announced.
OL,9,FThe rise is being capped at a level    
OL,10,Fwell below inflation, "to help reduce  
OL,11,Fthe impact on passengers", the         
OL,12,Ftransport secretary said.              
OL,14,FLabour called the hike - which is still
OL,15,Fthe second highest on record - "a sick 
OL,16,Fjoke", while a watchdog said passengers
OL,17,Fwere not getting value for money.      
OL,19,FFares will officially rise on 5 March  
OL,20,F2023.                                  
